PROPRIETARY AND CONFIDENTIAL

This repository and its contents — including configuration files, documentation,
and all associated materials — are the property of the National AIDS & STI Control
Programme (NASCOP), Ministry of Health, Government of Kenya.

PERMITTED USE
Access to and use of this repository is restricted to personnel who have been
expressly authorised by NASCOP. Authorised users may use this software solely
for HIV programme monitoring, reporting, and analysis activities in support of
the national HIV response.

RESTRICTIONS
Unauthorised persons may not access, use, copy, modify, merge, publish,
distribute, sublicense, or sell copies of this software or any part thereof.
Authorised users may not:
  - Attempt to re-identify de-identified or pseudonymised data
  - Use programme data for commercial purposes
  - Share access credentials (Bearer tokens) with unauthorised persons
  - Export or transmit raw programme data outside of approved channels

DATA PROTECTION
All data accessible through this tool is governed by the Kenya Data Protection
Act, 2019 (No. 24 of 2019) and applicable NASCOP data sharing policies. Users
are legally obligated to handle data in accordance with these frameworks.
Violations may result in revocation of access and legal liability under
Kenyan law.

DISCLAIMER
This software is provided "as is", without warranty of any kind. NASCOP and the
Ministry of Health, Government of Kenya shall not be liable for any claim,
damages, or other liability arising from the use of this software.
